{"questionId":"9067444","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Propene is an important starting material for many products. The following shows some compounds which can be made from propene, C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><br>Propene (C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>) → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Write an equation for the complete combustion of the compound C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O formed in (a)(iv).</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">2C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O (l) + 9O<sub>2</sub> (g) → 6CO<sub>2</sub> (g) + 8H<sub>2</sub>O (g)<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O (l) + 4.5O<sub>2</sub> (g) → 3CO<sub>2</sub> (g) + 4H<sub>2</sub>O (g) ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067444","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.c(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Write an equation for the complete combustion of the compound C3H8O formed in (a)(iv).","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.1 Introduction to the particulate nature of matter and chemical change","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}